This is a very simple program using recursion to solve
sudoku puzzles. Puzzles are passed into the program via space delimited
9x9 text files. Blank cells are represented by '0'.

Build Instructions:
    - Requires: CMake >= 3.28
    - Requires: g++-14, MSVC 17 (VS 2022), or clang++-18
    - Requires: ninja-build

    $ cmake -G Ninja -B build -S .
    $ cmake --build build --target all

Run:
    $ ./build/bin/solver -i ./example/puzzle.puz 

